Progress creates the illusion that we are moving toward deeper knowledge when, in fact, imperfect theories constantly lead us astray.
In his book Enlightenment Now (2018), Steven Pinker describes a second assault on science from within mainstream scholarship and the arts.
In our new era of Enlightenment, we need Romanticism again.
The biggest tug-of-war is not between science and religious institutional power, but rather between the primal connection to nature and scientific institutional power.
But the tensions between Romanticism and the soldiers of the original Enlightenment are rising up again.